fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.query

Class MogwaiQuery

  • Object
    • MogwaiQuery
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ATLQuery, GremlinQuery, OCLQuery

    public abstract class MogwaiQuery
extends Object
    Provides an abstract API to specify Mogwai queries that can be executed by an AbstractQueryProcessor.

    This class defines the methods any query has to implement in order to be processed by an AbstractQueryProcessor. Default implementation of some methods are provided to ease integration.

    Note: MogwaiQuery instances are not associated to a specific ModelDatastore, they are used as an abstract layer that can be processed on any compatible(s) ModelDatastore(s) (see process(AbstractQueryProcessor, List, Map).

    Instances this class can be created using concrete implementations of the fluent AbstractMogwaiQueryBuilder API.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    AbstractQueryProcessor, AbstractMogwaiQueryBuilder

        public QueryResult process(AbstractQueryProcessor<? extends MogwaiQuery> processor,
                           ModelDatastore datastore,
                           Map<String,Object> options)
                    throws QueryException
        Executes the query with the given AbstractQueryProcessor on the provided ModelDatastore.

        This method is a convenience wrapper for process(processor, Arrays.asList(datastore), options).

        Parameters:
        processor - the AbstractQueryProcessor used to compute the query
        datastore - the ModelDatastore to compute the query on
        options - a Map containing query execution options
        Returns:
        a QueryResult representing the output of the executed query
        Throws:
        QueryException - if the provided processor cannot compute the query
